Class Session

java.lang.Object
session.Session
public class Session extends Object
Models a tutoring session on a specific course Each tutoring session is solely associated with a course and a tutor.

Initially no date and time are associated with a session, but these may be set or changed at any time.

No students are initially associated with a session, but any number may be added as needed.

    • Session

      public Session(Course course, Tutor tutor)
      Creates a tutoring Session. If either parameter is null, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown. The date, time, and students are initially not assigned.
      Parameters:
      course - the subject matter for this tutoring session
      tutor - the person who will teach the course material
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if any parameter is null
      Since:
      1.3

      public void setSchedule(String date, String startTime, long duration)
      Sets or changes the scheduled date, time, and duration.
      Parameters:
      date - The date of the session in the form YYYY-MM-DD
      startTime - The time of the session in the form HH:mm (24-hour clock)

    • toString

      public String toString()
      Represents the session topic, date and time, tutor, and student(s). The format is as follows. 
      
Session on <course> at <date, time, duration>.
  Tutor: <tutor>
  Students: <student1>, <student2>, ...
      If the session is not yet scheduled, the date and time is reported as "at an unspecified date".

      If no students have yet enrolled in this session, "Students:" is replaced with "No students are assigned to this session".

      Overrides:
      toString in class Object
      Returns:
      the resulting Complex number
      Since:
      1.0
